## Player Skill Ratings (Stable Traits Only)

### James Maddison

**Strengths (0–100)**
- Ball Progression: 82
- Press Resistance: 78
- Chance Creation: 88
- Tactical Intelligence: 85

**Weaknesses (0–100)**
- Defensive Positioning: 62
- Physicality: 55
- Consistency: 68

**Why this matters tactically:**
- Spurs rely heavily on Maddison for central creation.
- When he is pressed out, Spurs struggle to create centrally.

---

## Team Tactical Identity

### Build-up Profile
- Primary build-up route: Wide → half-space
- Press resistance level: 64
- Risk tolerance: Medium–High

### Defensive Profile
- Preferred block: High → mid
- Press triggers: Backward passes, sideline traps
- Line height: High

### Transition Profile
- Attacking transitions: Direct, vertical
- Defensive transition weakness: 72

---

## Team Strengths & Weaknesses (0–100)

### Strengths
- Pressing cohesion: 76
- Physical duels: 78
- Second balls: 82
- Counter-attacking: 80
- Set pieces: 69

### Weaknesses
- Central progression: 58
- Low-block chance creation: 60
- Aerial defending: 63
- Midfield coverage: 65
- Build-up under press: 62

---

## Preferred Formations (Historical Prior)

| Formation | Likelihood | When Used |
|---------|------------|----------|
| 4-3-3 | 0.45 | Default |
| 4-2-3-1 | 0.30 | Protect central zones |
| 3-4-3 | 0.15 | vs strong wide teams |
| 4-4-2 | 0.10 | Chasing control / duels |

---

## Manager Profile

Manager: Ange Postecoglou
- Tactical philosophy: High line, proactive football
- Willingness to change shape: Medium
- In-game adaptability: 68
- Rotation aggressiveness: Low–Medium

---

## Known Matchup Vulnerabilities

| Opponent Style | Problem Caused | Why |
|---------------|---------------|-----|
| Physical mid-block | Loss of central control | Limited press-resistant midfielders |
| Strong aerial teams | Ineffective wide crossing | Low crossing efficiency |
| Low block | Chance creation issues | Reliance on transitions |

